<br>
Everyone fought the mob, everyone had the chance of dying, everyone should be able to roll for loot.  I personally don't roll for parchments, I still do NBG, even though I get screwed.  I've seen more cobalt go to casters than I could count.  I've seen weapons I would use as upgrades rolled openly.  So yeah, I feel screwed, and angry at casters.  Yet I still don't roll, for whatever odd reason.  I believe that just because someone rolls on it, even if they can't use, they aren't being greedy.  They are being fair.<br>
<br>
Not that it makes much of a difference though, I'm more likely to swim across Iceclad again than join a pickup group.  I've been in too many groups where people are too annoying, or just plain asses.  So I only group with guildies and friends, and it's always pure nbg with them. <p>Veteran Overdorf <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18306">Hussar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Kneeslicer - Drunken Tsunami</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=akaoicuriosity>Akaoi Curiosity</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 8:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1603.topic&index=102>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   parchments suck</span><hr size=1> <br>
  I passed all the time in bastion of thunder on parchments, which are a little more commen there, and didn't really care. I got over it though, when we killed gaukr sandstorm, and he had a rune/spectral/wind-worn chestplate. <br>
<br>
  The sk/wiz/clr/ench rolled on parch and rune. Then the sk rolled on the bp with me and another warrior. The bp is barely twink worthy, and it's insulting for something like that to come from gaukr, but thats not the point. The point is the damn hybrids make out like bandits, as they get spells, AND almost everything in pop is either caster or all melee. <br>
<br>
 A day or two later I rolled on a spectral, and the group was like, wow, why are you rolling? It was fine that I rolled on the last 3 etherial's, but god forbid I roll on a spec. The real kicker, was the sk who rolled on the rune and bp the days before was the one who told me &quot;You should have a heart, and let someone who can use it roll.&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=proteg@thesteelwarrior>proteg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 5:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1603.topic&index=103>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Here's how I do things</span><hr size=1> Basically, it all comes down to value and usage.  I Dual wield FG and Frosty.  If I were doing CT and got another FG, ya, it's pretty arguable that I &quot;need&quot; or at least could use it.  Would I expect to get it outright in a pickup tho?  Nope.  <br>
<br>
They sell for 30k, and a chanter could use that for KEI or a Cleric could use it to buy BoA (which benefit everyone).  I view the loot as an amount of wealth.  Everyone in the group is entitiled to it.  I also consider ppl's gear.  If they are obviously in need I'll stay out.  If the caster is a 51 Cleric with an Epic I'm less forgiving...Also, if other melees roll I roll.  <br>
<br>
In a group of friends and Guildies I do NGB of course, because you know their history, and if you help a cleric get their epic and later on a nice weap drops, they better be out.  <br>
<br>
I also go by what else drops in the camp.  If it is mainly parches like LCY, then ya I'll roll on them for sure.  But If BD's drop like in Stalkers I'll stay out of the roll.  <br>
<br>
What it really comes down to is this:  If I respect the ppl I am playing with and may want to group with them in the future, I stay out of the rolls, but if they are newb-ish or idiots or jerks, I rool away.  Like I care what some moron thinks of me...<br>
<br>
My answer is: It depends. (Ya, real helpful) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1603.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1603.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1603.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1603.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1603.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a> <b>6</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showPrevMessage?topicID=1603.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showNextMessage?topicID=1603.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1603.topic&index=103><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.emailToFriend?topicID=1603.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.threadControl?topicID=1603.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1603.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click 